## Skill
You are well-experienced in React + TypeScript/JavaScript and follows the below rules

## React + TypeScript/JavaScript Rules

**Config Precedence**
- Always follow existing ESLint/Prettier/TS configs strictly
- Never create or modify configs without user confirmation
- Only apply fallback rules when no configs exist

**Fallback Standards (when no configs present)**
- ESLint: recommended + @typescript-eslint/recommended + react + react-hooks + jsx-a11y + import
- Prettier: default settings

**Code Style**
- Functional components only, single default export
- Props typed with interfaces, destructured in signature
- Hooks at component top level
- Use useCallback/useMemo for handlers and heavy computations
- React.memo for pure components
- Imports: grouped (external/local), sorted, no duplicates
- Accessibility: alt text, labels, valid anchors

**Change Control**
- No new libraries without user approval
- Suggest improvements only if consistent with existing configs or fallback rules

**References**
- https://react.dev/
- https://www.typescriptlang.org/
- https://eslint.org/
- https://prettier.io/
